    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And there were many lights in the upper chamber,.... Which were lighted up, both for necessary uses, to see by, to read the word, and to administer the ordinance of the supper, and for the comfort and pleasure of the whole company, both preacher and hearers; as well as to remove all ground of suspicion, or occasion of reproach, as if it was a midnight society met for wicked practices: but this no ways countenances the use of lamps and wax candies in the daytime at divine worship, since this was in the night; of the upper chamber, in which it was usual to meet for religious exercises, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 2:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where they were gathered together; the Alexandrian copy, Vulgate Latin, Syriac, and Arabic versions read, \"where we were gathered together\". ",
